@tym-oao. Ok I see the problem and solution. We use a FrozenOrderedDict which thankfully *is* hashable. But the problem is when we have default values that are normal dict. Like `DictParameter(default=dict(blah="foo"))`. One way to fix this:

 1. Add test case in execution summary code
 2. Run test and see it fails as expected
 3. (the fix): Go to this code https://github.com/spotify/luigi/blob/31d9d81291ac697721594856613a653b5c2f6162/luigi/parameter.py#L747-L803, To `DictParameter` class add a `normalize` method. Ensuring that it's converts it's input to a value of type `FrozenOrderedDict`. Then the parameter-values will actually be hashable.
 4. Run tests and hopefully it passes.

